hayai
------------------------------------------
hayai is a C++ framework for writing benchmarks for pieces of code along the
lines of the normal approach for unit testing using frameworks such as
googletest.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libgcc1-6.4.0-5
  libhayai-devel-1.0.2-1bl1
  libhayai0-1.0.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-5
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  libtool-2.4.6-5
  make-4.2.1-2
  python-2.7.14-1
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Canonical website:
  https://bruun.co/2012/02/07/easy-cpp-benchmarking

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/nickbruun/hayai/archive/v1.0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack hayai-1.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./hayai-1.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/hayai-1.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/hayai-1.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhayai0-1.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhayai-devel-1.0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

